    "However, HigherHRNet requires a high-quality dataset with an extensive corpus of training data to fully learn pose patterns and relationships.",
    "DEKR 3 adopts a decoupled approach to regress the positions of human keypoints, transforming the pose estimation task into multiple independent keypoint regression problems.",
    "However, the decoupled regression method may face challenges in handling global consistency.",
    "5 propose the Self-Adaptive Heatmap Regression (SAHR) method and the Weighted Adaptive Heatmap Regression (WAHR) method to address challenges related to changes in human size and ambiguous human keypoint labels.",
